73 contribution rate applicable to that quarterly period and may implement penalties for employers
74 who fail to make contributions as required by this section.
75 (2) In order to reduce the administrative costs of collection of contributions, the director
76 shall, to the extent possible, use any existing procedures implemented by the department to make
77 similar collections. Amounts collected pursuant to this section shall be deposited in the
78 Commonwealth Care Trust Fund, established in section 2OOO of chapter 29.
79 (3) Before depositing the amounts, the director may deduct all administrative costs
80 incurred by the department as a result of this section, including an amount as determined by the
81 United States Secretary of Labor in accordance with federal cost rules. Except where inconsistent
82 with this section, the terms and conditions of chapter 151A that are applicable to the payment
83 and collection of contributions shall apply to the same extent to the payment and collection of
84 any obligation under this section.
85 (e) An employer aggrieved by a determination of the director with respect to its liability
86 for the fair share employer contribution or with respect to the amount it is required to pay may
87 appeal such determination within 60 days and in the form and manner as specified by the
88 department.
89 (f) The department and the health policy commission under chapter 6D may
90 waive or mitigate an employer's fair share contributions, fines, interest and related fees.
91 (g) Pending a fair share contributions appeal decision pursuant to subsection (e),
92 the department shall not continue to accrue or collect interest, penalties or fees on the fair share
93 contribution.
