94 (h) The department or any entity of the commonwealth shall not take any funds
95 out of an employer's bank account if the employer has filed a fair share contributions appeal
96 pursuant to subsection (e) or is in the process of mediation and is awaiting a decision.
97 (i) The department's help center staff shall not request identifying information
98 from an employer that is seeking assistance from the department helpline, nor shall the staff
99 share customer information with the audit department staff. No information recorded by the
100 helpline may be used in an audit proceeding or be used to initiate an audit.
101 (j) Upon completion of a hearing on an appeal with respect to an employer's
102 liability for the fair share employer contribution or to the amount it is required to pay, the
103 department shall render a written decision within 90 days.
104 (k) The department shall promulgate regulations necessary to implement this section. In
105 promulgating regulations defining the term “contribution” under this section, no proposed
106 regulation by the department, except an emergency regulation, shall take effect until 60 days
107 after the proposed regulations have been transmitted to the joint committee on health care
108 financing and the joint committee on financial services.
109 SECTION 2. Section 1 shall take effect upon either: (i) the repeal of 26 U.S.C. §4980H;
110 or (ii) a determination by the secretary of the executive office of health and human services that
111 the provisions of federal law under the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act requiring
112 applicable large employers to offer minimum essential health insurance coverage under an
113 employer-sponsored plan to full-time equivalent employees or make a shared responsibility
114 payment to the Internal Revenue Service, known as the shared responsibility provisions,
115 employer mandate or pay or play provisions” is eliminated or no longer enforced.
